# 2. IMPLEMENT EVENT-DRIVEN ARCHITECTURE

Stop relying on direct service-to-service calls.

Everything important should emit domain events.

Examples:

VehicleCreated

VehicleUpdated

VehicleDeleted

TripStarted

TripCompleted

MaintenanceScheduled

MaintenanceCompleted

FuelAdded

ExpenseCreated

BookingApproved

BookingRejected

ReminderTriggered

InspectionCompleted

InsuranceExpired

DocumentUploaded

DriverAssigned

DriverRemoved

Events should automatically trigger workflows.

Example:

MaintenanceCompleted

↓

Update vehicle status

↓

Update analytics

↓

Update reports

↓

Notify manager

↓

Schedule next maintenance

↓

Audit log

↓

Generate invoice

↓

Update dashboard

No duplicated workflow logic.

---

# 3. IMPLEMENT CQRS

Separate reads from writes.

Instead of:

VehicleService

Create:

VehicleCommandService

VehicleQueryService

Commands should only modify data.

Queries should only retrieve data.

This improves:

* scalability
* caching
* optimization
* reporting
* maintainability

